<br>
At level 45, I only had 5 pieces left.  At level 49, I'm down to just needing 3 pieces: CoM Torch, Kedge Staff, and Sky Crown.<br>
<br>
The epic quest is not for everyone to do.  It takes a great deal of time, and in a mage's case, a great deal of patience (killing the same mobs over and over for a rare drop).  But the magician epic can be done over the entire level range of the magician.  It can easily be started at level 20.  That's when I started mine.  My group in South Karana, tracking down Quillmane.  And I eventually got my pegasus cloak, after about 3 kills.<br>
<br>
If a person knows he/she wants to complete the epic, and starts early on, and pairs his/her normal experience camps with the epic camps needed for quest, it's very conceivable one would have all the pieces needed, and just need to level up to lvl 51 to do the final turn ins.<br>
<br>
I feel yer pain about Magi P'Tasa tho.  It took me 6 times in Hate before I ever saw him up.  But that one time he was up, he had staff.  And I looted it, and am now VERY close to completing the epic.  I've killed Phinny 6 times now.  I've killed Neh'Ashir 4 times.  I have a sky crown available for trade (guild is trading it's sky crown for 3 jade reavers).<br>
<br>
